name: GovernmentOfThePrincipalityOfLiechtenstein
definition: semi-constitutional monarchy headed by the Prince of Liechtenstein, with an elected parliament that enacts the law, as well as being a direct democracy, where voters can propose and enact constitutional amendments and legislation independently of the legislature
label: Government of the Principality of Liechtenstein

name: AustrianEntity
definition: federated sovereignty and polity that is Austria
label: Austrian entity

name: GovernmentOfTheFederalRepublicOfGermany
label: Bundesrepublik Deutschland
definition: democratic, federal parliamentary republic led by a chancellor, where federal legislative power is vested in the parliament, consisting of the Bundestag and the Bundesrat

name: JurisdictionOfGermany
label: German jurisdiction
definition: jurisdiction of the judiciary of Germany, whose civil law system is based on Roman law with some references to early Germanic law, headed by the Bundesverfassungsgericht (German supreme court) responsible for constitutional matters

name: GermanEntity
label: German entity
definition: federated sovereignty and polity that is Germany

name: GovernmentOfTheFrenchRepublic
label: Gouvernement de la République française
definition: unitary semi-presidential constitutional republic, built on strong representative democratic roots, based on the Constitution of the Fifth Republic which was approved in 1958

name: JurisdictionOfLiechtenstein
definition: jurisdiction of the judiciary of Liechtenstein, the system of courts and tribunals which interpret and apply the law in Liechtenstein, including the Regional Court at Vaduz, the Princely High Court of Appeal at Vaduz, the Princely Supreme Court, the Administrative Court, and the State Court
label: jurisdiction of Liechtenstein

name: BelgianEntity
label: Belgian entity
definition: federated sovereignty and polity that is Belgium

name: JurisdictionOfTheNetherlands
label: jurisdiction of the Netherlands
definition: jurisdiction of the judiciary of the Netherlands, the system of courts which interprets and applies the law in the Netherlands

name: GovernmentOfTheGrandDuchyOfLuxembourg
label: Government of the Grand Duchy of Luxembourg
definition: representative democracy that is a unitary, parliamentary constitutional monarchy, headed by the Grand Duke, which is the world's only remaining sovereign grand duchy

name: JurisdictionOfAustria
definition: jurisdiction of the judiciary of Austria (österreichische Justiz), consisting of general courts (ordentliche Gerichte) and courts of public law (Gerichte öffentlichen Rechts)
label: jurisdiction of Austria

name: SwissEntity
definition: federated sovereignty and polity that is Switzerland
label: Swiss entity

name: JurisdictionOfSwitzerland
definition: jurisdiction of the Federal Supreme Court, Federal Criminal Court, Federal Administrative Court, and the Federal Patent Court representing the judiciary branch at the federal level in Switzerland
label: jurisdiction of Switzerland

name: GovernmentOfTheSwissConfederation
label: Government of the Swiss Confederation
definition: federal semi-direct democracy under a multi-party presidential directorial republic, which represents a confederation of 26 cantons and communes with executive, legislative and judiciary branches

name: LiechtensteinerEntity
label: Liechtensteiner entity
definition: sovereign state and polity that is Liechtenstein

name: JurisdictionOfBelgium
definition: jurisdiction of the judiciary of Belgium, which is based on civil law and originates from the Napoleonic code, including the Court of Cassation and the courts of appeal, one level below
label: jurisdiction of Belgium

name: JurisdictionOfFrance
definition: jurisdiction of the judiciary of France, which is part of the Ministry of Justice based on a civil legal system, headed by the Court of Cassation and Council of State
label: jurisdiction of France

name: GovernmentOfTheRepublicOfAustria
definition: federal, representative democratic republic, with nine states, whose head of state is the Federal President (Bundespräsident), and head of the federal government is the Federal Chancellor (Bundeskanzler)
label: Government of the Republic of Austria

name: GovernmentOfTheKingdomOfBelgium
label: Government of the Kingdom of Belgium
definition: federal parliamentary constitutional monarchy, whose head of state is the king, though with limited prerogatives

name: JurisdictionOfMonaco
label: jurisdiction of Monaco
definition: jurisdiction of the judiciary of Monaco, the system of courts and tribunals which interpret and apply the law in Monaco, including the Monegasque Supreme Court, one of the highest courts of law in the city-state of Monaco for judicial appeals as well as ensuring the constitution of Monaco is upheld

name: JurisdictionOfLuxembourg
label: jurisdiction of Luxembourg
definition: jurisdiction of the judiciary of Luxembourg, the system of courts and tribunals which interpret and apply the law in Luxembourg, including three lower tribunals (justices de paix; in Esch-sur-Alzette, the city of Luxembourg, and Diekirch), two district tribunals (Luxembourg and Diekirch), and a Superior Court of Justice (Luxembourg), which includes the Court of Appeal and the Court of Cassation

name: FrenchEntity
label: French entity
definition: sovereign state and polity that is France

name: NetherlandsEntity
definition: sovereign state and polity that is the Netherlands
label: Netherlands entity

name: GovernmentOfTheNetherlands
label: Government of the Netherlands
definition: parliamentary constitutional monarchy with a unitary structure, with its monarch as head of state

name: MonegasqueEntity
definition: sovereign state and polity that is Monaco
label: Monegasque entity

name: GovernmentOfThePrincipalityOfMonaco
definition: constitutional monarchy with the Sovereign Prince of Monaco as head of state, and a Minister of State as the head of government, who presides over a five-member Council of Government
label: Government of the Principality of Monaco

name: LuxembourgerEntity
label: Luxembourger entity
definition: sovereign state and polity that is Luxembourg
